#show: recipe.with(title: "Bean Soup, Rice Cooker")[
  - Dried beans
  - Beef or sausages
  - 1 onion
  - 1 tomato
  - Salt, to taste#Footnotes.bean-seasoning
  - 1 pinch cumin
  - Cilantro, to taste
  - 2 tbsp. butter
  - Ghost pepper (optional)

  *Yields multiple bowls.*
]

== The Night Before (Optional#Footnotes.bean-soaking)

+ Rinse beans in cold running water.
+ Marinade meat if desired.
+ Soak beans in water in rice cooker overnight, 12-24 hours.#Footnotes.bean-stinking Beans
  should be no taller than a quarter of the rice cooker before soaking.

== The Day of the Meal

+ Rinse beans (again).
+ Place beans in rice cooker, add water to nearly maximum capacity, and turn rice cooker
  on.
+ Dice onion, ghost pepper, cilantro. Add all ingredients *except meat* to pot.
+ Keep pot boiling for 2 hours, or until beans are desired consistency. In the meantime...
+ Cook meat! Fry it, bake it, whatever.#footnote[Just don't boil it. I have faith in you.]
+ When broth is done, add meat to broth. Serve immediately.

== Trivia

